articles.headline: LSU's Morrow helped off court in SEC tournament vs. Texas
articles.description: LSU star Aneesah Morrow was helped off the floor during the third quarter of Saturday's Southeastern Conference semifinal game against No. 1 Texas after rolling her left ankle.

images.name: LSU's Aneesah Morrow exits the game in the third quarter
images.caption: Aneesah Morrow was helped off the court after an apparent foot injury in the third quarter vs. Texas.

articles.headline: Iriafen's 17 points send No. 2 Southern Cal past Michigan 82-70, into Big Ten title game
articles.description: — Kiki Iriafen scored 17 of her 25 points in the second half Saturday, JuJu Watkins added 20 points and each pulled down 11 rebounds to send No. 2 Southern California past fifth-seeded Michigan 82-70 and into the Big Ten championship game.

images.name: Avery Howell knocks down a three to push USC ahead
images.caption: JuJu Watkins sets up Avery Howell to drain a crucial 3-pointer to boost USC.

articles.headline: Londynn Jones scores 22 to help No. 4 UCLA rout No. 13 Ohio State 75-46 and reach Big Ten title game
articles.description: — Londynn Jones made six 3-pointers and scored a season-high 22 points Saturday, leading No. 4 UCLA to a 75-46 rout over No. 13 Ohio State in the Big Ten Tournament semifinals.

articles.headline: Staley says the Gamecocks keep their eyes on the prize
articles.description: Dawn Staley explains that South Carolina stays motivated because the goals always remains the same: to earn the SEC title and the No. 1 overall seed in the NCAAs that should come with it.

images.name: Staley says the Gamecocks keep their eyes on the prize
images.caption: Dawn Staley explains that South Carolina stays motivated because the goals always remains the same: to earn the SEC title and the No. 1 overall seed in the NCAAs that should come with it.

articles.headline: Edwards explains how every Gamecock makes an impact for them
articles.description: Joyce Edwards talks about how South Carolina's bench is able to be so effective after her 21-point outing and advancing to the SEC Championship.

images.caption: Joyce Edwards talks about how South Carolina's bench is able to be so effective after her 21-point outing and advancing to the SEC Championship.

articles.headline: No. 5 South Carolina advances to SEC Tournament title game with 93-75 win over No. 10 Oklahoma
articles.description: — Joyce Edwards scored 21 points, and No. 5 South Carolina advanced to the Southeastern Conference Tournament championship game with a 93-75 win over 10th-ranked Oklahoma on Saturday.
